verses.roman:
tabe sei mahāprabhura caraṇa vandiyā
sabāra caraṇa vandi' cale hṛṣṭa hañā

synonyms: tabe—thereafter; sei—the governor; mahāprabhura—of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; caraṇa vandiyā—after worshiping the lotus feet; sabāra caraṇa vandi'-offering respect to the feet of all the other devotees; cale—departed; hṛṣṭa hañā—being very pleased.
translation: After this, the Mohammedan governor offered prayers to the lotus feet of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu as well as to the lotus feet of all His devotees. After that, the governor departed. Indeed, he was very pleased.
